text.tspan: Alcohol consumption per person, United States, 1850 to 2013
Alcohol consumption per person, measured in litres of ethanol per person per year. From 1920-1933 there was a ban
on the production, importation, transportation, and sale of alcoholic beverages (prohibition) in the United States.
Source: National Institute on Alcohol Abuse and Alcoholism (NIAAA)
